'''c6.org''' was an international [[media art]] and [[street art]] collective centred in [[London]] active from 1997 to 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.widewalls.ch/artist/dotmasters/|title=Dotmasters|website=Widewalls.ch|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>
The group combined graffiti, new media art and performance art with political commentary throughout the 90s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/1418809.stm|title=Anatomy of a backlash 2|date=17 July 2001|accessdate=4 November 2018|website=News.bbc.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metamute.org/editorial/articles/artists-non-residence|title=Artists in Non-Residence - Mute|website=Metamute.org|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>
The founder of the group Leon Sessix also makes street art and stencil graffiti under the name Dotmasters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2010/04/play/street-art-dealer-spray-it-sell-it|title=Street Art Dealer: Spray it, sell it|website=Wired.com|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>
